tafsir[8]{c,v,t}:
  77,2,"And He also takes an oath on the severely blowing winds."
  77,3,"And also on the winds that disperse the rain."
  77,4,"And He also takes an oath on the angels that descend with that which differentiates between truth and falsehood."
  77,5,"And He also takes an oath on the angels who descend bringing revelation."
  77,9,"The sky will suddenly crack because of the angels descending from it."
  77,11,"And the Messengers will be gathered for a fixed time."
  77,14,"O Messenger! What do you know of the day of separation?"
  77,16,"Did I not destroy the previous nations when they disbelieved in Allah and rejected their Messengers?"